# Brand — Aakhara

## Identity

Aakhara (आखाड़ा) is a voice sales-training roleplay platform for Business Development Executives. Every BDE walks into the arena, spars with an AI prospect, and walks out sharper before the real call.

## Story

In the Indian tradition, an आखाड़ा is a wrestling arena — a sacred space for disciplined practice. Wrestlers train daily on packed earth, building strength, technique, and reflex before any real bout. Aakhara brings that ethos to sales: every BDE practices voice-to-voice with an AI prospect — handling objections, refining discovery questions, sharpening close — before they ever pick up a real call.

## Voice

- **Disciplined, grounded** — this is serious craft, not a game
- **Respectful of tradition** — Sanskrit-rooted but accessible globally; never orientalist
- **Practical** — every feature ties to "are you closing more deals?"

### Do
- "Practice the call before the call."
- "आखाड़ा — the arena where every BDE earns their pitch."
- "Earned reps. Real wins."

### Don't
- Gamify with points/badges/leaderboards (cheapens the practice ethos)
- Overuse Sanskrit (one word — आखाड़ा — earns its place; don't pile on)
- Compare to "Duolingo for sales" (it's roleplay, not gamified flashcards)

## Audience

- **Primary**: India-based B2B SaaS BDE teams (10–500 reps)
- **Secondary**: global-remote BDE teams that need accent + objection practice
- **Tertiary**: solo founders practicing investor pitches (lighter use case)

## Positioning question (operator decides in S11C interview)

Two paths:
1. **Standalone product** — separate brand, separate billing, own GTM
2. **Vagary Voice sub-product** — Aakhara as a vertical inside Vagary Voice (sales-training vertical alongside other voice-AI use cases)

The voice stack (Deepgram + ElevenLabs + Gemini/OpenAI) is shared with Vagary Voice either way; the question is brand + go-to-market.

## Domain

`aakhara.com` (pending purchase) — preferred. Backup: `aakhara.app` or `aakhara.io`.
